<br>
And the Versus Mode. Oh, the versus mode. There are ten different Orbital Frames to choose from: 4 versions of Jehuty, 2 versions of Anubis, and the 4 boss OFs. Each character has its own advantages over the rest, and a couple have extremely useful special skills (Anubis can use Zero Shift with a push of the L1 button, and the Vic Viper can change between Aero-mode and Humanoid mode).<br>
<br>
The only faults in Versus mode is the lack of some of the stages in the original. As cool as it is to fight in space, or some of the huge battlegrounds featured, they still left out the Park battleground (a halo of buildings where you fight an OF in the first game) and the Cargo Room (where you fight Viola in the first game, moving in and out of the cmpletely destructible moving structures). Still, that's more nitpicking from me. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :hat --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/pimp.gif ALT=":hat"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Extra Missions are an assortment of different challenges that vary in difficulty. You only have maybe 60% opened at first (after beating the game once), and then you have to find the Ex Mission icons to add more. You choose the OF you want to challenge with, then you navigate through the subcategories to find missions that pretty much cover every skill you need to develop to become a master with the OF controls. (To tell the truth, I suck at Grab attack missions <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :hat --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/pimp.gif ALT=":hat"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ).<br>
<br>
The idea behind Ex Missions is to open 100% of the missions, then complete 100% of the missions, and then get a high score on 100% of the missions. Takes a lot of committment, but it's fun. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :hat --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/pimp.gif ALT=":hat"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
